Package: pltimer
Type: Package
Title: Timing of Copy Number Aberrations and Driver Mutations with Plackett-Luce Models
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Naser Ansari-Pour, Iliana Peneva
Maintainer: Iliana Peneva <iliana.peneva@bdi.ox.ac.uk>
Description: An implementation of timing of the occurrence of copy number aberrations and driver 
    mutations using different implementations of the Plackett-Luce model. It starts with preprocessing
    the subclones data, output from Battenberg, then identifying the enriched regions in the cohort 
    and post-processing of the segments in the enriched regions to remove artefacts. It implements
    Plackett-Luce model, using the PlackettLuce and PLMIX R packages to infer the most likely temporal
    ordering of the driver events across the cohort.
Depends: R (>= 3.5.2)
Imports: 
    data.table (>= 1.12.8),
    dplyr (>= 0.8.4),
    ggplot2 (>= 3.2.1),
    reshape2 (>= 1.4.3),
    cowplot (>= 1.0.0),
    gtools (>= 3.8.1),
    tidyr (>= 1.0.2),
    copynumber (>= 1.22.0),
    BSgenome.Hsapiens.UCSC.hg19 (>= 1.4.0),
    PlackettLuce (>= 0.2-9),
    PLMIX (>= 2.1.1)
